parameters:
Oh? Is that the group of castaways? Good to see you're all
unharmed and looking well. Don't go getting on a ship again,
you hear?

It's no use fussing about it now. I'm just doing my fishing
work as usual. Haha

Smoke is rising from the peak of Mount Fuji. Could it be
erupting again, like it did five years ago?

Mwoooah!? Offshore--!? A huge black ship is coming
offshore...!

Grandpa's been getting senile lately, saying that black
ships are coming to Uraga... Really, it's quite troubling...

Don't you need precious fruits and ornaments? They're items
not sold anywhere else.
Thanks. I'm wishing you luck on your journey.

It's quite nice to die in a place you love. I stay here
because I love this village. So, is there anything you want?
Thanks. I'm wishing you luck on your journey.

What? You want to go to Mujou Island? It's far, so I'll take
you there for 2000 mon.\$
Please! I want to go to Mujou Island once more.

Are you serious? Can't be helped. I'll put some spirit into
rowing the boat. Be careful not to get seasick.
--Karin paid 2000 mon and boarded the boat!\$
Speak to Kachou and the others
It seems your health has fully recovered.

Sorry to keep you waiting. I'm all better now. Let's head
for Edo.
...Well then, I shall take my leave here.
Eh? Kokuyou Tengu-san, you're not coming with us to Edo?

Ah, in my case, being a well-known figure with a
recognizable face, it wouldn't suit me to disguise myself,
nor will I go to Edo. I plan to return to the life of a
mountain ascetic as before.
I see. I thought for sure you'd come with us to Edo...

Is that so? It's a shame it's so sudden. If we hadn't met
you, escaping from Mujou Island would have been impossible.
We're seriously grateful for your guidance.

Thank you for everything, Tengu-san. The way you controlled
the ghost octopus was truly magnificent.

Kachou and Kisanosuke--you two also live well together. Live
modestly so the officials from the magistrate's office don't
find you.

When it comes time to part, it's strangely sad... I'm also
grateful, Kokuyou Tengu. I'll never forget the time we
shared sea bream soup together.

Hmm. I feel the same That sea bream soup was delicious!
Farewell then. Karin, the rough and skilled fisher-girl--
live well and never turn to thievery again.
--Kokuyou Tengu parted ways with Karin and the others.
We did it-! We've safely made it back to Edo~!

We've successfully escaped! Take that, officials of Mujou
Island, eat your hearts out! We've accomplished the great
feat of returning from exile!

It feels so nostalgic... It's been two years for me, but the
streets of Edo haven't changed much.

Kachou-san, let's hurry to Fukagawa. I'm sure your mother is
waiting on the bridge even today.

...But... meeting mother now... somehow, it feels very
awkward...

What are you talking about, Kachou-san? I'm with you. Let's
meet your mother and put her mind at ease!

That's right, Kachou-san. Your mother has been waiting all
this time! Come on, let's hurry before the sun sets--!

--Karin and Kisanosuke pulled Kachou by the arm and headed
towards Fukagawa.

There she is! Look, Kachou-san! Your mother, she's been
waiting!

I'm sorry. I escaped from the island to come see you...
Mother... I'm sorry for worrying you all this time...

What are you saying?! It was originally because I needed
medicine for my illness that you went to the pleasure
district and got caught up in that incident... It's my
fault... Ahh... The real Kachou... I really wanted to see
you...
Uuh! Mother--! Waaah~ I've wanted to see you so much too!
--Kachou embraced her mother while shedding tears.
I'm glad for you... Kachou-san... meeting your mother...

Ah. I can't help but tear up myself... It's a reunion
between a mother and daughter who've been apart for two
years.

Do you remember me? It's Karin. I was also exiled to Mujou
Island, so I escaped together with Kachou-san. Ahaha...

Karin-san, you're so strong... If it weren't for her, I
wouldn't have been able to make it back here... She's my
great benefactor.

Thank you, Karin-san. Thanks to you, I was able to see my
daughter again. I don't know how to thank you enough...

No, no... It was worth waiting on the bridge all this time.
I'm really glad that both of you could be reunited.

Nice to meet you. Uh... I'm not a suspicious person. I'm
just a wanderer who escaped from the island with Kachou-san
and Karin-san. Heh heh heh!
This person is Kisanosuke-san. He's my... husband.

Yes, that's right... I told you before, didn't I? When we
get back to Edo, I want Kisanosuke-san to marry me...

R-really? Kachou-san...? Are you sure about me being your
husband...?

Yes... It's less suspicious for officials if we're married,
so let's live together, just the three of us from now on.

Thank you! I'm so happy to be able to become husband and
wife with the woman I love, Kachou-san! So... please take
care of me from now on!

Just when I thought my daughter had come back, she brought a
husband with her too... Ahaha. I'm doubly surprised. Tears
of joy are a wonderful thing, aren't they?

I'm happy for you, Mother. Well then, I'll be heading home.
I've been away for so long, I want to see Oei-san too. Both
of you, be happy together

Karin-san. It's thanks to you that we made it this far.
Seriously, thank you! Let's both be careful not to get
caught by the officials!

Let's meet again once things have settled down. I'm glad I
met you. Thank you so much, Karin-san--
--Karin parted ways with Kachou and Kisanosuke with a smile.
(I'm glad Kachou-san could reunite with her mother.)

...(Now, what should I do from here... Going home or
visiting Oei-san seems dangerous.)

...Hey, isn't it about time you showed yourself? No one's
around here. We can talk, just the two of us.

...Hmm. You noticed someone was tailing you. You've improved
since the bandit subjugation in Kandai Village, Nezumi
Komachi.

Ever since arriving in Edo, I've felt someone's gaze on me.
So it was you who was following me?

That's right. But I must say I'm surprised. It's
unprecedented for a banished criminal to escape from Mujou
Island and make it back to Edo. Even as a thief, that's
quite the spirit. I'll give you that much credit.

...! Are you here to capture me? An underling of the
magistrate's office--?

No. We belong to a different jurisdiction than the
magistrate's office. Since then, our organization has become
even busier. We could use a cat's paw or even a mouse's
help... that's where we're at.

No need for words from here on--first, let me test your
strength. We can fight with all our might here where there
are no prying eyes.

My name is Yugiri--I challenge you to a one-on-one duel.
Agreed?
...So you really want to cross swords with me? Fine...
--Karin transformed into her Nezumi Komachi persona!

Talking big isn't necessary--I don't fully understand your
reasons, but I'll accept the fight you've picked! In return,
I'll crush you!

No need for brave words either. Here I come, Nezumi Komachi.
Let's have a fair fight--!

--Tch! (She's more skilled than I thought...! Did I
underestimate her because I thought she was just a thief!?)
This is the finishing blow! Yaaah--!!
It's my trump card... Everyone, throw the chains--!
Eh! Reinforcements--!? They were waiting on the roof...!?
Now's my chance! I've got you in the flank--!

Rest assured, it was a blunt strike. It would be troublesome
for us if you died--

--Karin was struck hard in the abdomen and fell to the
ground!

Hmph. I'm somewhat disappointed. If that's the extent of
your skill, perhaps there was no need to lure you out.
I haven't lost yet! I can still... fight!
I'll acknowledge your spirit. But... this is the end.

--Karin was struck hard in the abdomen and fell to the
ground!

Good, she's calmed down. You guys, take Nezumi Komachi to
the mansion.

...! (Ninja... a troop of them...? Where are they taking
me...)
--Karin was taken away by the ninjas!

"We are searching for an escaped criminal. If you find
anyone suspicious, report it immediately."
Yes...! (This is bad... I need to escape to Edo quickly.)

We've had unseasonal storms recently, but it finally feels
like it's cleared up. Now we can go out to fish.
